tags: this is literally how i recognised this song
i’ve watched this episode way too many times
summary: We were watching telly and they put Uprising by Muse as the end song for an episode, and it started with the opening notes, and...
body:
We were watching telly and they put Uprising by Muse as the end song for an episode, and it started with the opening notes, and I’m like thinking and then, “Muse!” And my sister nods and it took me another moment and I go “Uprising!” And she’s trying to figure out how I knew the name just from the opening tunes Cos I don’t really listen to Muse much and in my head I’m all, “No it’s not, it’s Uprising, this is what it should’ve sounded like. Muse’s Matt Bellamy once cancelled a whole day of interviews because he said an asteroid was going to hit the earth. Not the first time he’s tried to pull that stunt. He once claimed the world was going to go supernova and burst into a ball of fiery destruction just to get out of PE. Matt Bellamy has been plagued recently by a flurry of letters from fans claiming they would commit suicide unless he sleeps with them. BARROWMAN!”


Yes, I recognised the song Cos it was in David’s episode of Never Mind the Buzzcocks. Yes.

title: David Tennant and Peter Davison Join The Line Up For The Muppets Take The O2
body:
David Tennant and Peter Davison Join The Line Up For The Muppets Take The O2

This is a Muppet news flash. It’s time to put on makeup, it’s time to light the lights as the most sensational, inspirational, celebrational, muppetational show hits London – and they’re bring a couple of Doctors with them too!

Making sure that there will definitely be a Doctor in the house (“waka waka”), David Tennant and Peter Davison will join the Kermit the Frog & co as they take to the O2…
